            <scopecontent>
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                                 <p>In this letter of Feb. 24, 1918, C. H. Hiller, a U.S. Army officer in France, describes his duties as &quot;Town Major.&quot; He was responsible for billeting troops and protecting the community.</p>
                                 <p>Prof. Jack Nortrup donated this photocopy to the Library in 1971.</p>
                        </scopecontent>
            


